///////////////////////////////////
// Using Android.gitignore
///////////////////////////////////

If you’re not using GitHub, you can still add your own .gitignore file to your repo.  To do this for your Android project, follow the steps below:

1. Copy the attached “Android.gitignore” file into the root of your repository.

2. Rename “Android.gitignore” to “.gitignore”. OS X will warn you about making the file hidden, just accept it.

3. Commit the .gitignore file to your repo.

Congrats! All extra generated files will now be ignored.